[[File:Nam_Chorios.jpg|thumb|250px|A Force Storm on [[Nam Chorios/Legends|Nam Chorios]].]]
'''Force storm''' was a [[Force power/Legends|Force power]] that presumably combined [[Telekinesis/Legends#Force Whirlwind|Force Whirlwind]] and [[Force lightning/Legends|Force lightning]] to create something akin to a dry tropical storm. It was most likely intended to be used in concentration in a small area.

Also known as "Summon Storm," this power [[Telekinesis/Legends|telekinetically]] manipulated the nearby atmospheric conditions to whip the weather around the user into a frenzy. A skilled user could create storm conditions in areas up to several kilometers in diameter, lasting for hours at a time.

Sheets of rain reduced visibility and thoroughly soaked anything in the area, while driving winds whipped foliage and hurled loose objects about. When combined with the random lightning strikes, the storm could be hazardous enough to ground flying vessels and dramatically interfere with any combat or other activities in the area.

This ability could only be used outdoors, and was constrained by the local climate. Though a user could not conjure a rainstorm in a desert, a dangerous sandstorm was certainly not out of the question.

While not inherently a [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] ability, it was most commonly used by darksiders; such as [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] and the [[Nightsisters/Legends|Nightsisters]] of [[Dathomir/Legends|Dathomir]]; due to the power's wide-ranging and indiscriminately destructive nature.

Some versions of this power were much less damaging than Force lightning.<ref name="Fate of the Jedi: Backlash">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Backlash]]''</ref>

[[Darth Plagueis/Legends|Darth Plagueis]] called a Force storm as one of his last efforts to try and fend off [[Palpatine/Legends|Darth Sidious]], when Sidious betrayed and killed him. However, Sidious's [[Force barrier/Legends|Force defense]] was sufficient to withstand this.<ref name="Darth Plagueis novel">[[Darth Plagueis (novel)|''Darth Plagueis'']]</ref> Luke Skywalker conjured one of these about himself as he gave himself to the Force while fighting in the [[Battle of Yuuzhan'tar|reconquest of Yuuzhan'tar]].<ref name="The New Jedi Order: The Unifying Force">''[[The New Jedi Order: The Unifying Force]]''</ref>

